title: LilGuyBrainwashed
---
<<wait 2>>
<<fadeIn SceneSampleEvents>>
<<wait 2>>
// Still same Bridge environment bridge asset
//////////////////// Play Ascension track
I speed my way onto The Bridge's onramp, weaving through self-driving cars and a corporate megabus. 
It's just a few miles before I reach Root Town, where Frisscity's high-tech gadgets lose signal and hold no power over me.
///////////////// Slide in Lil Guy’s character on right and set his expression in AGENTS-mode
Nubs: …
///////////////// Slide in Luna from left and set her pose to neutral and her expression to surprised
Luna: W-What the hell?!
The AGENTS logo dominates Nub's screen as his lifeless body continues to cling onto my neck as I race past another bus.
Luna: Nubs!? Hey, buddy, wake up!
The all-seeing eye bares holes into the back of my head. A new voice takes over Nub's.
// Is there a way NOT to call Maxx’s sprite to appear when he says the following stuff? Just show the dialogue box and then label it as “Maxx” speaking?
Maxx: There you are.
Luna: Shit, he can track me…!
I hear a motor roar in the distance—it could only be one gigachad.
Maxx: Won't be long before I catch up.  
My breath stalls, and sweat starts rolling down my neck.
Luna: (I knew there was a cost to shoving it to Maxx and those corporate assholes.)
Luna: (But I'm basically screwed!)
Luna: (Was this choice even worth it…?)
<<jump Cybergulls>>
===


title: Cybergulls
---
//////////////// SFX gulls short version and let it play in its entirety, but don't loop it. 
Luna: !!!
It's the cybergull gang. Only the most notorious animals to have evolved from Frisscity's chemical runoff and swallowing metal scraps whole. 
Their shrieks ring out as I approach Root Town. 
They're like the first line of defense from letting outsiders into the town…
/////////////// Change Luna’s expression to happy (?) depends on the art 
…And they're the key to ditching Maxx for good.
I hear tires screeching and then, in a blink of an eye, I see Maxx riding right beside me.
Maxx: Boo. 
Luna: …
We're both speeding down the road, neck and neck.
///////////////// Change Maxx’s expression to angry
Maxx: Aren't you gonna pull over now? I got you! 
Luna: Not yet.
Suddenly, I veer off and make a hard left turn onto another highway. It's the turn only a local would know. 
////////////////// SFX gulls long version and let it play in its entirety, but don’t loop it.
Maxx: Tch!
Maxx doesn't make the turn in time and continues straight…right into the cybergulls' lair.
I stop my bike at the edge of the shoulder lane, watching as the birds descend on him on the highway below.
////////////////// Can we animate jiggling the sprite somehow? Even if it’s up and down like a jump. Something to imply that he’s struggling 
Maxx: No no no no NOOOOO! Not the face! Not the JAW!!
The birds continue to pick at him and anything that glows, which includes both Maxx and his precious state-of-the-art motorcycle.
////////////////// More animation jiggling/jumping of the sprite
Maxx: AHHHHHHHHHHHHRRRRGHHHH!!!
////////////////// Fade Maxx’s sprite slowly away, like a dissolve or opacity effect
Whatever is left of Maxx and his motorcycle remains on the highway, like roadkill. The cybergulls slowly disperse back into dusk.
A sharp noise buzzes from Nubs and I turn to look at him.
/////////////////// Show Lil Guy pose and expression as worried
Nubs: H-Huh? 
Luna: Nubs! You're back!
Nubs: What happened…?
<<fadeOut SceneSampleEvents>>
<<jump BridgeResolution>>
